his boxing gym. Accomplishing all this at the young age of 18. <br>
<br>
One day he decides to pick a fight with Sato. Who is known to be a black belt in Tae Kwon do and a master of many other forms of martial arts. Saddly Fuji gets his ass handed back to him. Knowing that his reputation has been stained, Fuji demands a rematch with Sato. Fuji goes to Sato's dojo and fights Sato durring one of his lessons. Fuji is then defeated again, and is scolded by Sato to not challenge him again because his skill isnt on par with his.<br>
<br>
As Fuji is leaving the dojo, He is confronted by the Master of the dojo. He tells Fuji that he has the spirit of a great fighter, but to defeat Sato he must understand him and go through all the of training and hardships that he went through in order to be his equal. Fuji is then offered to join the dojo and take lessons there. He accepts the offer.<br>
<br>
Fuji then starts his Training, he is at first turned off by the lack of challenge in the lower belts and is disiplined by The Master for being to rough with them. Fuji doesnt want to open up to this new style of fighting and only thinks about beating the snot out of Sato. As time goes on Fuji starts to open up to all of the philosophies, disiplines and training that karate masters all have to go through in order to be great fighters. While mixing his boxing style with karate and making a style of fighting all his own.<br>
<br>
Along the way Fuji and his new found gym will come across various opponents that threaten the well being of others. Challenging other dojo's for pride. And even battling Fuji's own former boxing partners who think Fuji has betrayed them.<br>
<br>
With a theme to it is to open up to new things or sumthing. well thats my story idea. <p>WWW.Xcelldesign.com<br>
